                            <comment id="63329" author="adam.causey" created="Fri, 11 Feb 2011 12:10:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure if Refactoring is the correct type or if this is a bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="70155" author="berserkpi" created="Tue, 6 Sep 2011 12:06:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So, beyond the packages names. Does exist a problem doing this refactor? Perhaps a license issue?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess I will create my own View. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But, It would be nice if we could get this &quot;out of the box&quot; in the near future.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="110130" author="bclozel" created="Fri, 28 Nov 2014 02:52:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We won&apos;t update this dependency to its new groupId, as the license changed:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;com.lowagie&lt;/tt&gt; was MPL + GPL&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;com.itextpdf&lt;/tt&gt; is now AGPL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This new license is viral and that change can be a real issue for Spring developers.&lt;br/&gt;
Also, note that the official &lt;tt&gt;com.lowagie&lt;/tt&gt; versions stop at &lt;tt&gt;2.1.7&lt;/tt&gt; and that &lt;tt&gt;4.2.*&lt;/tt&gt; seem to be an unofficial fork not supported by the itextpdf community. I&apos;ve tested our integration with &lt;tt&gt;4.2.1&lt;/tt&gt; anyway and it works fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
